toms and electrons."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2,1],"segment":{"end_index":1078,"start_index":992,"text":"This innovative approach was detailed in a study published in *Nature Communications*."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":1271,"start_index":1079,"text":"In testing across 71 experiments, the AQuaRef method demonstrated the ability to generate higher-quality structural information while maintaining or improving agreement with experimental data."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":1479,"start_index":1272,"text":"Notably, the system successfully resolved the proton positions in the human protein DJ-1, which is associated with some forms of Parkinson's disease and has been historically challenging to model accurately."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[3],"segment":{"end_index":1640,"start_index":1481,"text":"The intersection of quantum computing, AI, and optimization is a key focus of the upcoming Quantum Artificial Intelligence & Optimization (QAIO) 2026 workshop."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[3],"segment":{"end_index":1871,"start_index":1641,"text":"The workshop, part of the 18th International Conference on Agents and Artificial Intelligence (ICAART) held in Marbella, Spain, on March 8, 2026, brings together researchers and industry leaders to discuss the latest advancements."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[3],"segment":{"end_index":2083,"start_index":1872,"text":"The workshop's agenda underscores the critical research areas in the field, including Quantum Machine Learning, Quantum Optimization Algorithms, Hybrid Quantum-Classical Computing, and Quantum Generative Models."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[4],"segment":{"end_index":2340,"start_index":2085,"text":"In a significant development for the foundational software of quantum AI, Canadian quantum computing company Xanadu has partnered with South Korea's Electronics and Telecommunications Research Institute (ETRI) in a two-year collaborative research project."}},{"grou