[1],"segment":{"end_index":1724,"start_index":1466,"text":"The development of hybrid quantum-classical systems is expected to be the dominant approach for practical applications, combining the strengths of both technologies to overcome the current limitations of quantum hardware, such as error rates and scalability."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[1],"segment":{"end_index":1875,"start_index":1725,"text":"This synergy will be crucial for tailoring quantum software to specific industry needs in sectors like finance, biopharmaceuticals, AI, and logistics."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[1],"segment":{"end_index":2040,"start_index":1876,"text":"For instance, in finance, quantum algorithms are poised to revolutionize portfolio optimization and risk management by processing multiple variables simultaneously."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":2285,"start_index":2122,"text":"AI will be instrumental in optimizing quantum systems by assisting with qubit calibration, error reduction, and the automated design of efficient quantum circuits."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":2502,"start_index":2286,"text":"Conversely, quantum computing is expected to enhance AI by accelerating model training and optimization, enabling more efficient data representation, and potentially improving the speed and accuracy of AI algorithms."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":2699,"start_index":2503,"text":"Quantum Machine Learning (QML) is emerging as a critical field, with a heavy focus on hybrid quantum-classical models like Variational Quantum Algorithms (VQAs) and Quantum Neural Networks (QNNs)."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[3],"segment":{"end_index":2904,"start_index":2701,"text":"Looking at the broader landscape, 2026 is seen as a crucial year for organizations to begin their transition to post-quantum cryptography to safeguard their infrastructure against future quantum threats."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[3],"segment":{"end_index":3098,"start_index":2905,"text":"The convergence of increasingly powerful quantum processors and agent-based AI systems is expected to accelerate progress and risk, with machines operating at speeds beyond human comprehension."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[3],"segment":{"end_index":3279,"start_index":3099,"text":"While the prospect of Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) being powered by quantum computers raises complex questions, some projections suggest AGI could emerge as early as 2026."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[4],"segment":{"end_index":3514,"start_index":3281,"text":"Key players like Google, with its introduction of the Willow chip and the quantum echoes algorithm in 2025, are paving the way for practical applications in 2026 in fields such as cryptography, materials science, and AI optimization."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":3698,"start_index":3515,"text":"The collaboration between large tech companies and specialized quantum startups is anticipated to further accelerate innovation and commercial adoption of hybrid AI-quantum solutions."}},{"grounding_chunk_indices":[2],"segment":{"end_index":3852,"start_index":3699,"text":"These solutions are expected to begin tackling previously infeasible problems, such as real-time climate modeling and large-scale logistics optimization."}}],"search_entry_point":{"rendered_content":"<style>\n.container {\n  align-items: center;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  display: flex;\n  font-family: Google Sans, Roboto, sans-serif;\n  font-size: 14px;\n  line-height: 20px;\n  padding: 8px 12px;\n}\n.chip {\n  display: inline-block;\n  border: solid 1px;\n  border-radius: 16px;\n  min-width: 14px;\n  padding: 5px 16px;\n  text-align: center;\n  user-select: none;\n  margin: 0 8px;\n  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\n}\n.carousel {\n  overflow: auto;\n  scrollbar-width: none;\n  white-space: nowrap;\n  margin-right: -12px;\n}\n.headline {\n  display: flex;\n  margin-right: 4px;\n}\n.gradient